$interpreted: Demihuman Patrolman: Halt!
Demihuman Patrolman: Who are you?
Demihuman Patrolman: What are you doing in Atlas!?
Leah: Outta my way, I haven't the time!!
Demihuman Patrolman: Wah... I won't back down. The pride of the demihumans is in my hands!
Leah: What pride! Can't you see I'm a demihuman too!
Demihuman Patrolman: Shut it!! How dare you mock us demihumans' pride!
Leah: Ahh, spoken like a true subordinate of Nigel's! Very good! Now take me to him, this instant!
Demihuman Patrolman: Hmph, who's to say if those bunny ears of yours are even real or not? There's barely any demihumans left at the Rune Academy, aside from a pair of rabbit twins—
Lio: —Sis!!
Leah: Lio? What're you doing here?
Lio: Look who's talking! Aren't you supposed to be at the Academy?
Demihuman Patrolman: ...Y-y-you...
Fredrica: Yup~ That pair of rabbit twins you're looking at right now~
Leah: And Fredrica's here too...
Jerome: Miss Leah, we're looking for Nigel too. But he seems to be occupied right now. Is it an emergency?
Leah: What!? What'll we do, the others are—
Fredrica: Don't panic, the man with the horns isn't here, but I am~ I'm listening~
Fredrica: Ugh~ A woman's youth is so precious. Leave it to a man to waste her time!!
Jerome: Miss Leah, which way do we go now?
Leah: This way!
Lio: Don't bully my Sis!
Jerome: That's a lot of monsters...
Leah: Yeah, more than when I came through here just a moment ago. I hope Annie and the others are all right...
Leah: Of course Nigel's nowhere to be found at a time like this. Where the hell'd that idiot go!!
Fredrica: Even so, I know that the Rune Academy's responded to the monster carnage by dispatching every teacher and student they have to places all over to help.
Fredrica: But it can't be so bad that they need to ask Atlas for help, can it?
Leah: Hoo~ This wasn't the original plan. There've been so many monster attacks lately, we're running out of medicines.
Leah: My classmates and I were only responsible for taking the herb cart back to the Academy, so that Professor Clovis could take over...
Jerome: But you were held up by a mob of monsters near here, and thought you'd ask Nigel to send somebody to help, is that it?
Leah: I'm a demihuman, so it was up to me to go to Atlas for help. Annie and the rest stayed to look after the cart...
Leah: It should be somewhere near here, but I don't see anybody. If anything's happened to them... it'll be all my fault...
Lio: Sis...
Carla: Wah~ Amazing!!
Betty: Weird... My heart's beating so hard and fast...
Annie: I feel it, this must be destiny~ Rescuing us girls from the jaws of defeat! Our mysterious knight in shining armor!♥
Leah: Right up ahead, let's hurry up and take a look!
